page.title: 01GENERAL VIEW OF THE AREA
page.content: THE HIGHEST POINT IN THE AREA IS{93 {METRES ABOVE SEA LEVEL.}RELIEF IS GENTLY{UNDULATING.}THE GENERAL IMPRESSION IS OF ROLLING FARM LAND. THE AREAS OF WOODLAND ARE INTERSPERSED BY TREES IN THE{HEDGEROWS.}THERE ARE TWO CHURCH TOWERS, COMMUNICATION MASTS ON HIGH GROUND. TREES ARE DISPERSED AND LINEAR. SCATTERED MIXED WOODLAND, FIELDS IRREGULAR IN SHAPE AND FORM A PATCHWORK OF COLOUR IN SPRING AND AUTUMN. ON MAJOR ROADS THERE ARE FARMHOUSES AND TIED COTTAGES. THERE ARE MEANDERING COUNTRY LANES. ONE LARGE FLAT AREA WHICH WAS USED AS AN AIR FIELD IN WORLD WAR 2. {by: {A.STEVENS { I.ARBUTHNOT
